<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>weissblau</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Heyokah<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: May 2001<br />
	Location: Halas
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I often have to go LFG on a raid, either when the raid is first forming or before/after a COH when the raid temporarily breaks up.  I hate getting tells from random people for LDON groups or whatever while the LFG tag is up.<br />
<br />
I played with the LFG window and set some filters, but they didn't seem to work.  Last night I finally figured out why (I was setting the filters and then using /lfg on instead of clicking the LFG ON button).  So since I finally got it right, I thought I'd share.<br />
<br />
Here's the scoop.<br />
<br />
1. Type /lfg to bring up the LFG window (don't use /lfg on).<br />
<br />
2. Click "Additional Filters"<br />
<br />
3. Click "Only include these guilds in my search results".  Use the ADD button to add your guild or the guilds in your raiding alliance.<br />
<br />
4. Click "Only players who match my posted filters can query me".<br />
<br />
5. Close the additional filters dialog<br />
<br />
6. Click the LFG ON button on the LFG window.  NOTE: YOU CANNOT SIMPLY CLOSE THE LFG WINDOW AND USE THE /LFG ON.  The filters will not apply if you use /lfg on.<br />
<br />
I tested this last night with my non-guilded trader in the bazaar, and I could not see my character as LFG even though I had the LFG tag on at a raid.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=529003">Twoflower Tourist</a> - <a href="http://www.unionofpower.org">Union of Power</a><br />
68 Heyokah<br />
Rodcet Nife</div>
	
	
