	<p>/em pulls out rant stick...<br />
why the hell would you go LFG on a raid?<br />
is this a closed guild raid ? or an open naggy/vow type raid ?<br />
if so, doesn't your guild know you enough to invite you by name and not class/lvl ?<br />
i see this alot on drinal with uber guilds, i think its kinda gimpy.<br />
my guild isn't that uber but we can do saryn,tt, and a few other pop raid targets and such, but it always buggs me when i wanna exp grind and need a clr lfg, and i see 9+ clerics lfg in VEX THAL...<br />
my guild has somewhere near 35-45 people on during raid nights, and yet we still seem to invite/know all of our members, is the uber guild heirarchy about being "nameless_leet_player_01" ??<br />
<br />
i would like some feed back to my rant, hope i didn't offend.</p>
	
	
	
