<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Gloriana</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	NEW SITE crucible.samanna.net<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jul 2000<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I guess every guild has their own system for grouping up. In the past, raid leaders in my guild would create groups and spam the raid channel with the group leaders and who they should invite. This method took a LOT of time.<br />
<br />
We now do a simpler method. We arrive at the raid destination and then we just group ourselves up. Clerics normally start a group, ask the raid leader for a group leader invite and then...invite the people lfg.<br />
<br />
Of course, we know all our members, but it's a lot easier to do a quick /who lfg and pick up the 5 guildies lfg then to look at the raid window, look at the /who guild list and then try to figure out who is lfg.<br />
<br />
caveat - some raids require special group formations, of course.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
		<div class="smallfont"><a href="report.php?s=dcc0c6dbab3f3cd4941f8f081eb6adb8&amp;postid=208119">Report Post</a> | IP: <a href="postings.php?s=dcc0c6dbab3f3cd4941f8f081eb6adb8&amp;do=getip&postid=208119">Logged</a></div>
	
