	<!-- message -->
	<p>Kurth, no offense taken here, although for someone asking a question you are quite brash....<br />
<br />
The guild I am in uses /lfg all the time. When a raid is forming the objective is to get people grouped asap. Why have group leaders run around targetting and inviting people randomly? We all know each others classes, etc. but it definitely cuts down on time to just do /w lfg and target folks. Once everyone is in folks get moved around quickly and effectively to set group structure.<br />
<br />
Twoflower, I haven't bothered to use the lfg window on a raid. I will give it a try and see if it makes sense. Thanks for posting that.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
