	<p>I think the /lfg is a useful work around for the trounle of setting up groups in a raid. Not in a guild myself but you sometimes have to work with what eq gives you and this is a good example. The one thing that would make both the people doing ldon (like me) and the raiders happy is put in a comment line about raiding. This prevents random tells from Butcherblock and helps the LDONers quickly eliminate people that they cant use for their group. just the way i see it...</p>
	
	
	
