	<p>my guild isn't particularily tight knit.  I mean, people come and they have gone, some have been there for freaking ever and some are brand new, but we use LFG at raids as a grouping tool.  Usually we just have healers invite folks.  Someone starts the /raid and invites all clerics as group leaders who in turn invite everyone else.  <br />
<br />
Course special raiding circumstances need special groups, but these are usually just modifications of the random groups that result from above method.</p>
	
	
	
