	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />on drinal i know a few kids in the uber guilds who tell me after 1-2 years of playing with the same people that they don't even know thier birthdays, when they last spoke, or anything.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>This has to be the most bizarre thing I've read in a long time. What does this have ANYTHING to do with knowing whether or not someone has a group?<br />
<br />
I don't raid anymore, but when I did, you always went LFG during formation. There's no better way to find this out. Spamming LFG! in a guild or chat channel just makes spam. Turn on LFG, raid leader picks group leaders, group leaders send invites to people LFG, once the raid is formed, you can look at the raid window and do any fine tuning to group composition that might be needed. <br />
<br />
I could tell all of my guildmates apart with names turned off just by looking at them. I could not tell you the real names of a single person in my guild, nevermind irrelevant nonsense like their birthdays.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
