<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>thRover</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: May 2003<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>We usually have the healers form up groups too. But you get stragglers, 85'ers, some people are overlooked, afk, etc. Sometimes the raid leader announces groups in raid chat. I usually put lfg up anyway, after all it doesn't hurt anything. I always make sure to put "raid purposes" in my message so people know. I've only gotten one tell since I started doing that, it was from some guy who told me he'd been trying to get invited into a raid that way for 2 weeks, but they always turned him down. <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /> I can just imagine him sending tells to people waiting for invites asking if he can join the raid.<br />
On the other hand, many people use /lfg and do not give any message. If you are looking to fill an XP group that can be very annoying. I play on a pretty small server, so chances are you know the people and can tell what guild they are in and make the assumption that they are raiding. But it takes so little effort to make a message, why not just take the time to do it?</p>
	
	
	
