	Joined: Nov 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>gotta interject here. LFG tag for raiding is one of my biggest pet peeves, along with using raid say to ask for buffs. <br />
<br />
For some reason, guilds on my server just love to form their raids in Plane of Tranquility. Now, if you go LFG in Plane of Tranquility, what the hell do you think is going to happen? Some people don't use the new LFG tool, so putting a 'raiding' note next to your name is going to do jack.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /> In the past, raid leaders in my guild would create groups and spam the raid channel with the group leaders and who they should invite. This method took a LOT of time.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>This is the system my guild uses now. Now I don't mean to gloat, but I lead raids regularly (or am asked to set up groups) and forming groups is just trivial. First of all, my guild uses a chat channel for all raids, i.e. "aowraid" for an Avatar of War raid. The group-maker does a /list 1 or whatever number that channel is. There - he has a list of all people attending the raid.<br />
<br />
Clerics and druids start all groups. Match shaman with druid preferably, put one shaman in each group for shrink. MT/ST group gets first bard, secondary and tertiary bards group with rangers rogues and wizards. There. You're done.<br />
<br />
LFG tag? what does that do? you're going to hand by hand select each of 50 lfg raiders and put them together? That seems like a far more laborious process, and even MORE laborious would be the process of rearranging and messing with groups after they are made carelessly or selfishly without any coordination, swapping paladins around for group heals or shaman for shrink or bards for DS or SK's around for recourses, confusing and a waste of time.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
		<div class="smallfont"><a href="report.php?s=dcc0c6dbab3f3cd4941f8f081eb6adb8&amp;postid=208363">Report Post</a> | IP: <a href="postings.php?s=dcc0c6dbab3f3cd4941f8f081eb6adb8&amp;do=getip&postid=208363">Logged</a></div>
	
