	Joined: Aug 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>yeah, we use /lfg on too whenever we are raiding.  But, forming the raid in the zones that you are raiding in helps alot.  I mean, I have gotten the random tell for someone when I'm sitting in Time asking me if I wanted to join a PoV/BoT group, but i'm pretty nice about saying that i'm in the middle of raiding.<br />
<br />
What was said that is very true, is that when you are dealing with 60+ people at a raid, I'm not going to sit there and click on every damn person to figure out which one not grouped up if they don't have their lfg tag up, nor am I going to search over the raid grouped list figuring it out either.  If you want a group anytime soon, put /lfg up and make a proactive stance at asking someone who the group leaders are that still have room (this is a pet peeve of mine, hate having someone sit there in guild chat saying that they haven't gotten a group in 20 min when they have no clue who might be able to invite them).<br />
<br />
I've only been in my guild for approx. 6 months.  As a member of a prob 85+ guild, I can safely say that I know a good % of them, not all personally, but enough where Ihave talked to them on several occasions and I know who theyare.  Some better than others of course.  If you've played in a guild for 2 years and don't know some of the people, and they aren't either very new to the guild or someone that's returned after an extended absence, then something is wrong.</p>
	
	
	
